            </p>
            <main>
                <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-800">How to Create & Resize Ad Banners with AI</h1>
                <table>
                    <tr><th>The Problem</th><th>The AI Solution</th></tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Manually creating and resizing banners in Figma or Pixlr is a high-effort, long-winded bottleneck for Media Planners.</td>
                        <td>Use Gemini Advanced's image generation to create professional ad banners from a text prompt and ask for instant resizes.</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
                <div class="tag-container">
                    <span class="tag tag-purple"><strong>Primary Roles:</strong> Media Planners, Commercial Ops</span>
                    <span class="tag tag-purple"><strong>Tools:</strong> Gemini Advanced (standalone)</span>
                    <span class="tag tag-purple"><strong>Difficulty / Phase:</strong> Phase 3: Advanced AI</span>
                </div>
                <hr class="solution-hr">
                <h2 class="text-2xl mb-4 solution-h2">Step-by-Step Training Workflow</h2>
                <h3 class="text-xl mb-3 solution-h3">Step 1: Open Gemini Advanced</h3>
                <p class="mb-4">Go to the standalone Gemini web interface (<code>gemini.google.com</code>) that has image generation capabilities.</p>
                <h3 class="text-xl mt-6 mb-3 solution-h3">Step 2: Write a "Creative Brief" Prompt</h3>
                <p class="mb-4">Be specific, like you're briefing a designer.</p>
                <pre><code>Create an ad banner for [Merchant Name]'s "Summer Sale".
-   The banner should be 728x90 (leaderboard).
-   Use bright summer colors (yellows, oranges, light blues).
-   Include the text "Summer Sale" (large) and "Up to 50% Off" (smaller).
-   The style should be modern, clean, and photographic.
-   Generate 4 different options.</code></pre>
                <h3 class="text-xl mt-6 mb-3 solution-h3">Step 3: Iterate and Resize Instantly</h3>
                <p class="mb-4">Refine the generated images and resize them instantly.</p>
                <p><strong>Iteration:</strong></p>
                <pre><code>I like option 3. 
Can you make the blue text a bit darker so it's easier to read?</code></pre>
                <p class="mt-4"><strong>Instant Resizing:</strong></p>
                <pre><code>That's perfect. Now, take that exact design and resize it to:
-   300x250 (Medium Rectangle)
-   160x600 (Skyscraper)
-   320x50 (Mobile Banner)</code></pre>
                <h3 class="text-xl mt-6 mb-3 solution-h3">Step 4: Handle "In-Image" Text</h3>
                <p class="mb-4">If the AI struggles with text, ask it to leave a blank space where the text should go, and you can add it manually in Figma. This still saves 90% of the work.</p>
